# Sec Mapper

Sec Mapper is a production-oriented vulnerability intelligence scanner for dependency manifests and lockfiles.

It preserves backward compatibility with the original CLI commands while adding:
- layered vulnerability intelligence (local + optional live NVD/OSV)
- confidence scoring and false-positive controls
- reconciliation/discrepancy reporting across sources
- remediation and mitigation recommendations
- richer JSON/HTML/SARIF outputs plus a machine-readable API format
- web API + dashboard UI mode
- CI/CD and issue tracker integration hooks

## Key capabilities

- Dependency scanning for direct and transitive dependencies.
- Dependency path tracking to show why a vulnerable package is present.
- Source reconciliation and discrepancy reporting.
- Confidence labels:
  - exact version match
  - advisory-backed match
  - heuristic match
  - uncertain match requiring review
- System-state summary after scan:
  - what is currently vulnerable
  - what has a fix
  - what needs immediate upgrade
  - what can be mitigated
  - what is uncertain
- Safe-by-default PoC guidance (non-weaponized). Lab mode is explicit opt-in.

## Supported manifests

Currently supported through parser plugins:
- package.json
- package-lock.json
- requirements.txt
- poetry.lock
- Pipfile.lock
- pom.xml
- go.mod
- Cargo.toml

## Install

```powershell
python -m venv .venv
.\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
python -m pip install --upgrade pip
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

## CLI usage

Backward-compatible scan commands:

```powershell
python main.py samples\package.json
python main.py samples\requirements.txt
python main.py samples\package.json --lock samples\package-lock.json
python main.py samples\package.json --format json
python main.py samples\package.json --format html
python main.py samples\package.json --format sarif
```

New machine-readable API format:

```powershell
python main.py samples\package.json --format api
```

Fail pipeline on severity threshold:

```powershell
python main.py samples\package.json --lock samples\package-lock.json --format json --fail-on-severity high
```

Exit code behavior:
- 0: success / below threshold
- 2: threshold matched/exceeded
- non-zero otherwise: runtime or argument error

## Live intelligence sources

Default behavior is deterministic/offline-first using local advisory DB.

To enable live enrichment (OSV + NVD keyword source):

```powershell
$env:SEC_MAPPER_ENABLE_LIVE_INTEL="true"
python main.py samples\package.json --format json
```

Optional NVD API key:

```powershell
python main.py samples\package.json --nvd-api-key <key>
```

## Web UI and API

Run server mode:

```powershell
python main.py --serve --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8000
```

Open browser:
- http://127.0.0.1:8000

API endpoints:
- GET /health
- GET /
- POST /scan
- POST /jobs
- GET /jobs/{job_id}
- GET /jobs/{job_id}/report/{json|html|sarif|api}

Example scan request:

```json
{
  "manifest_path": "samples/package.json",
  "lock_path": "samples/package-lock.json"
}
```

## Output formats

- text: CLI-readable summary
- json: full structured report with confidence, evidence, status, and remediation
- html: dashboard with summaries, finding cards, and post-scan system state
- sarif: CI/Code Scanning integration
- api: machine-readable API payload for external platforms

## CI/CD integration

GitHub Actions workflow included:
- .github/workflows/security-scan.yml

It:
- installs dependencies
- runs JSON and SARIF scans
- enforces severity gate
- uploads SARIF and JSON artifacts

## Pre-commit

Config provided:
- .pre-commit-config.yaml

Scanner pre-commit helper:
- scripts/sec_mapper_pre_commit.py

## Issue tracker integration hooks

Implemented in src/integrations.py:
- GitHub Issues auto-ticket creation for high/critical findings
- Jira ticket creation hook

Environment variables:

GitHub:
- SEC_MAPPER_GH_TOKEN
- SEC_MAPPER_GH_REPO (owner/repo)

Jira:
- SEC_MAPPER_JIRA_URL
- SEC_MAPPER_JIRA_USER
- SEC_MAPPER_JIRA_TOKEN
- SEC_MAPPER_JIRA_PROJECT

## Security posture and false-positive controls

- Cross-source reconciliation (local, OSV, NVD when enabled)
- Advisory discrepancy surfaced instead of hidden
- Evidence required and attached to each finding
- Deterministic confidence scoring
- Duplicate clustering and merge of repeated findings
- Uncertain findings are explicitly labeled for manual review

## Mitigation workflow

Each finding reports:
- patch availability
- mitigation availability
- remediation recommendation
- status label

Status labels used:
- vulnerable
- fixed available
- mitigation applied
- mitigation recommended
- no patch available
- needs manual review
- low confidence / unverifiable

## Testing

Run all tests:

```powershell
python -m pytest -q
```

Current suite covers:
- parser behavior and plugin parsers
- transitive dependency handling
- scanner integration and report generation
- confidence and dedup behavior
- intelligence pipeline cache/discrepancy logic
- web API basic and async job flow

## Current limitations

- Live source matching from NVD keyword mode can be broad and may require manual review.
- Source code SAST rules are represented by architecture hooks and safe triage summaries, not full semantic code-flow yet.
- Issue tracker auto-sync of ticket status is hook-ready but depends on environment and policy wiring.

## Project structure (core)

- src/dependency_parser.py: parser plugins and dependency extraction
- src/intelligence.py: source adapters, normalization, cache/retries/rate-limit, discrepancy detection
- src/scanner.py: orchestration, matching, confidence, dedup, triage, remediation
- src/remediation_engine.py: remediation and system-state logic
- src/triage.py: deterministic AI-assisted triage layer hooks
- src/report_generator.py: json/html/sarif/api output generators
- src/web_api.py: API server and async scan jobs
- src/web/index.html: web dashboard UI
- src/integrations.py: issue tracker integration hooks

## Backward compatibility note

Existing commands and report formats remain supported. The architecture is extended rather than replaced.
